This article highlights the commitments made by various organizations to raise awareness and increase understanding of mental health. The Obama Administration has taken steps to improve mental health care, such as expanding coverage through the Affordable Care Act and supporting initiatives to help educators recognize signs of mental illness in students. The National Conference on Mental Health aims to increase understanding of mental health, and the Administration has launched mentalhealth.gov, a consumer-friendly website with tools and resources. Private sector and non-profit organizations have made commitments in areas such as launching awareness campaigns, educating students and adults about mental health, providing tools for healthcare providers, convening experts to reduce stigma, and starting conversations in faith-based institutions. These commitments aim to reduce stigma, improve access to treatment, and raise awareness about mental health issues.